---
title: Ratatouille Style Aubergine and Butter Beans with Greek Style Cheese, Pesto and Ciabatta Dippers
description: Originating in the French city of Nice and cooked throughout the Provence region, ratatouille is a dish made of Mediterranean vegetables such as aubergines, courgettes, peppers and onions that are stewed together. This dish takes inspiration from ratatouille for a more filling dinner that's bulked up with beans.
